The paper deals with the secure connectivity of wireless sensor networks, which is a topic that falls under the categories of cryptography (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also involves modeling and analyzing the performance of the pairwise key predistribution scheme, which is a topic that falls under the categories of information theory (cs.IT) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents results in the form of zero-one laws, which is a topic that falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
